<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="445" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1396,2033]" pageId="1" pageNumber="445">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1431,1456]" pageId="1" pageNumber="445">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Pygofer lobe apex acute spinelike (
<figureCitation box="[735,806,1431,1456]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 19" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[167,1421,376,1877]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,373,1900]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 19. Portanus hastatus sp. nov. 9 – 14, male genitalia. 9, genital chamber, lateral view. 10, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view. 11, connective and right style, dorsal view. 12, right style, lateral view. 13, aedeagus, lateral view. 14, aedeagus, caudal view. 15 – 19, female genitalia. 15, sternite VII, ventral view. 16, pygofer, lateral view. 17, gonoplac, lateral view. 18, valvula I, lateral view. 19, valvulae II, lateral view. All scale bars are 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/227163/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="445">
Fig. 
<number box="[790,806,1432,1456]" pageId="1" pageNumber="445" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
); aedeagus with pair of elongate dorsoapical processes (
<figureCitation box="[159,285,1468,1493]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 19" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[167,1421,376,1877]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,373,1900]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 19. Portanus hastatus sp. nov. 9 – 14, male genitalia. 9, genital chamber, lateral view. 10, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view. 11, connective and right style, dorsal view. 12, right style, lateral view. 13, aedeagus, lateral view. 14, aedeagus, caudal view. 15 – 19, female genitalia. 15, sternite VII, ventral view. 16, pygofer, lateral view. 17, gonoplac, lateral view. 18, valvula I, lateral view. 19, valvulae II, lateral view. All scale bars are 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/227163/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="445">
Fig. 
<number box="[212,285,1468,1492]" pageId="1" pageNumber="445" value="13.5" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="13.0">13–14</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="447" pageId="1" pageNumber="445" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1396,2033]" pageId="1" pageNumber="445">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,453,1503,1528]" pageId="1" pageNumber="445">Measurements (mm).</emphasis>
Male: body length, 
<number box="[678,730,1503,1528]" pageId="1" pageNumber="445" value="4.5">4.50</number>
; crown length, 
<number box="[902,954,1504,1528]" pageId="1" pageNumber="445" value="0.38">0.38</number>
; transocular width, 1.00; interocular width, 
<number box="[151,204,1540,1565]" pageId="1" pageNumber="445" value="0.5">0.50</number>
; maximum pronotum width, 1.00; forewing length, 
<number box="[847,900,1540,1565]" pageId="1" pageNumber="445" value="3.5">3.50</number>
. Females: body length, 
<number box="[1201,1254,1540,1565]" pageId="1" pageNumber="445" value="4.5">4.50</number>
; crown length, 
<number box="[151,266,1575,1600]" pageId="1" pageNumber="445" value="0.44" valueMax="0.5" valueMin="0.38">0.38–0.50</number>
; transocular width, 
<number box="[507,559,1576,1600]" pageId="1" pageNumber="445" value="1.1">1.10</number>
; interocular width, 
<number box="[797,849,1575,1600]" pageId="1" pageNumber="445" value="0.6">0.60</number>
; maximum pronotum width, 1.00– 
<number box="[1267,1317,1576,1600]" pageId="1" pageNumber="445" value="1.1">1.10</number>
; forewing length, 
<number box="[235,351,1612,1637]" pageId="1" pageNumber="445" value="3.625" valueMax="3.75" valueMin="3.5">3.50–3.75</number>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1396,2033]" pageId="1" pageNumber="445">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1647,1672]" pageId="1" pageNumber="445">Description.</emphasis>
Head (
<figureCitation box="[424,520,1647,1672]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1550,1573]" captionTargetBox="[179,1420,203,1520]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[163,1424,195,1527]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Portanus hastatus sp. nov. 1, dorsal habitus. 2, lateral habitus. 3, face. 4, crown, pronotum, and mesonotum. 5 – 8, Portanus phoenicius sp. nov. 5, dorsal habitus. 6, lateral habitus. 7, face. 8, crown, pronotum, and mesonotum." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/227162/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="445">
Fig. 
<number box="[476,520,1648,1672]" pageId="1" pageNumber="445" value="2.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="1.0">1–4</number>
</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view, with transocular width longer than crown median length; anterior margin angulate; frontogenal sutures reaching ocelli; texture shagreen. Pronotum as wide as transocular width; lateral margins angulate; dorsopleural carina inconspicuous; posterior margin straight; texture smooth with transverse striae. Mesonotum (
<figureCitation box="[500,599,1756,1781]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1550,1573]" captionTargetBox="[179,1420,203,1520]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[163,1424,195,1527]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Portanus hastatus sp. nov. 1, dorsal habitus. 2, lateral habitus. 3, face. 4, crown, pronotum, and mesonotum. 5 – 8, Portanus phoenicius sp. nov. 5, dorsal habitus. 6, lateral habitus. 7, face. 8, crown, pronotum, and mesonotum." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/227162/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="445">Fig. 1, 4</figureCitation>
) with scutum smooth and scutellum shagreen. Forewings (
<figureCitation box="[1272,1368,1756,1781]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1550,1573]" captionTargetBox="[179,1420,203,1520]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[163,1424,195,1527]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Portanus hastatus sp. nov. 1, dorsal habitus. 2, lateral habitus. 3, face. 4, crown, pronotum, and mesonotum. 5 – 8, Portanus phoenicius sp. nov. 5, dorsal habitus. 6, lateral habitus. 7, face. 8, crown, pronotum, and mesonotum." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/227162/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="445">
Fig. 
<number box="[1326,1368,1756,1780]" pageId="1" pageNumber="445" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2</number>
</figureCitation>
) with three closed anteapical cells, median anteapical cell slightly longer than others.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1396,2033]" pageId="1" pageNumber="445">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1828,1853]" pageId="1" pageNumber="445">Coloration.</emphasis>
Head and thorax (
<figureCitation box="[560,658,1828,1853]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1550,1573]" captionTargetBox="[179,1420,203,1520]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[163,1424,195,1527]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Portanus hastatus sp. nov. 1, dorsal habitus. 2, lateral habitus. 3, face. 4, crown, pronotum, and mesonotum. 5 – 8, Portanus phoenicius sp. nov. 5, dorsal habitus. 6, lateral habitus. 7, face. 8, crown, pronotum, and mesonotum." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/227162/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="445">
Fig. 
<number box="[616,658,1828,1852]" pageId="1" pageNumber="445" value="2.0" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.0">1–3</number>
</figureCitation>
) brown; venter brownish-yellow; some specimens with discolored areas at face. Crown (
<figureCitation box="[398,464,1863,1888]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1550,1573]" captionTargetBox="[179,1420,203,1520]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[163,1424,195,1527]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Portanus hastatus sp. nov. 1, dorsal habitus. 2, lateral habitus. 3, face. 4, crown, pronotum, and mesonotum. 5 – 8, Portanus phoenicius sp. nov. 5, dorsal habitus. 6, lateral habitus. 7, face. 8, crown, pronotum, and mesonotum." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/227162/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="445">
Fig. 
<number box="[452,464,1864,1888]" pageId="1" pageNumber="445" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
) with median line, apical triangular outline, lateral small spots, ivory. Pronotum (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1550,1573]" captionTargetBox="[179,1420,203,1520]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[163,1424,195,1527]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Portanus hastatus sp. nov. 1, dorsal habitus. 2, lateral habitus. 3, face. 4, crown, pronotum, and mesonotum. 5 – 8, Portanus phoenicius sp. nov. 5, dorsal habitus. 6, lateral habitus. 7, face. 8, crown, pronotum, and mesonotum." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/227162/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="445">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,163,1900,1924]" pageId="1" pageNumber="445" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
) with several ivory speckles. Mesonotum (
<figureCitation box="[659,726,1900,1925]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1550,1573]" captionTargetBox="[179,1420,203,1520]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[163,1424,195,1527]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Portanus hastatus sp. nov. 1, dorsal habitus. 2, lateral habitus. 3, face. 4, crown, pronotum, and mesonotum. 5 – 8, Portanus phoenicius sp. nov. 5, dorsal habitus. 6, lateral habitus. 7, face. 8, crown, pronotum, and mesonotum." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/227162/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="445">
Fig. 
<number box="[714,726,1900,1924]" pageId="1" pageNumber="445" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
) mostly ivory with paired large lateral round areas at anterior half and variable smaller maculae, discolored, appearing brown. Forewings (
<figureCitation box="[1038,1135,1935,1960]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1550,1573]" captionTargetBox="[179,1420,203,1520]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[163,1424,195,1527]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Portanus hastatus sp. nov. 1, dorsal habitus. 2, lateral habitus. 3, face. 4, crown, pronotum, and mesonotum. 5 – 8, Portanus phoenicius sp. nov. 5, dorsal habitus. 6, lateral habitus. 7, face. 8, crown, pronotum, and mesonotum." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/227162/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="445">
Fig. 
<number box="[1093,1135,1936,1960]" pageId="1" pageNumber="445" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2</number>
</figureCitation>
) translucent brown; veins marked with dark brown with small white spots; four hyaline regions on costal margin at apical half; apex completely dark brown. Female abdomen dark brown dorsally and brownish-yellow ventrally.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/227162/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="446" targetBox="[179,1420,203,1520]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1550,1604]" pageId="2" pageNumber="446">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,315,1550,1573]" pageId="2" pageNumber="446">FIGURES 1–4.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[322,507,1551,1573]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Portanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hastatus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[322,507,1551,1573]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="446">Portanus hastatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[514,596,1551,1572]" pageId="2" pageNumber="446" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[514,596,1551,1572]" pageId="2" pageNumber="446">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
1, dorsal habitus. 2, lateral habitus. 3, face. 4, crown, pronotum, and mesonotum. 5–8, 
<taxonomicName box="[201,411,1581,1604]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Portanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phoenicius" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[201,411,1581,1604]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="446">Portanus phoenicius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[417,497,1582,1603]" pageId="2" pageNumber="446" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[417,497,1582,1603]" pageId="2" pageNumber="446">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
5, dorsal habitus. 6, lateral habitus. 7, face. 8, crown, pronotum, and mesonotum.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1643,2028]" pageId="2" pageNumber="446">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,377,1643,1668]" pageId="2" pageNumber="446">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer lobe (
<figureCitation box="[545,614,1643,1668]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 19" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[167,1421,376,1877]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,373,1900]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 19. Portanus hastatus sp. nov. 9 – 14, male genitalia. 9, genital chamber, lateral view. 10, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view. 11, connective and right style, dorsal view. 12, right style, lateral view. 13, aedeagus, lateral view. 14, aedeagus, caudal view. 15 – 19, female genitalia. 15, sternite VII, ventral view. 16, pygofer, lateral view. 17, gonoplac, lateral view. 18, valvula I, lateral view. 19, valvulae II, lateral view. All scale bars are 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/227163/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="446">
Fig. 
<number box="[598,614,1643,1667]" pageId="2" pageNumber="446" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
), in lateral view, longer than high; subtriangular; posterior margin acute; few macrosetae on apex. Valve (
<figureCitation box="[528,613,1679,1704]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 19" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[167,1421,376,1877]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,373,1900]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 19. Portanus hastatus sp. nov. 9 – 14, male genitalia. 9, genital chamber, lateral view. 10, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view. 11, connective and right style, dorsal view. 12, right style, lateral view. 13, aedeagus, lateral view. 14, aedeagus, caudal view. 15 – 19, female genitalia. 15, sternite VII, ventral view. 16, pygofer, lateral view. 17, gonoplac, lateral view. 18, valvula I, lateral view. 19, valvulae II, lateral view. All scale bars are 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/227163/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="446">
Fig. 
<number box="[583,613,1679,1703]" pageId="2" pageNumber="446" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
), in ventral view, trapezoidal; longer than wide. Subgenital plates (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 19" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[167,1421,376,1877]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,373,1900]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 19. Portanus hastatus sp. nov. 9 – 14, male genitalia. 9, genital chamber, lateral view. 10, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view. 11, connective and right style, dorsal view. 12, right style, lateral view. 13, aedeagus, lateral view. 14, aedeagus, caudal view. 15 – 19, female genitalia. 15, sternite VII, ventral view. 16, pygofer, lateral view. 17, gonoplac, lateral view. 18, valvula I, lateral view. 19, valvulae II, lateral view. All scale bars are 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/227163/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="446">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,210,1715,1739]" pageId="2" pageNumber="446" value="9.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="9.0">9–10</number>
</figureCitation>
), in lateral view, extending posteriorly farther than pygofer apex; apical third slightly upturned; basal third with transverse unpigmented line; ventral surface with few uniseriate robust macrosetae and many long and fine microsetae at apical half. Connective (
<figureCitation box="[597,675,1787,1812]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 19" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[167,1421,376,1877]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,373,1900]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 19. Portanus hastatus sp. nov. 9 – 14, male genitalia. 9, genital chamber, lateral view. 10, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view. 11, connective and right style, dorsal view. 12, right style, lateral view. 13, aedeagus, lateral view. 14, aedeagus, caudal view. 15 – 19, female genitalia. 15, sternite VII, ventral view. 16, pygofer, lateral view. 17, gonoplac, lateral view. 18, valvula I, lateral view. 19, valvulae II, lateral view. All scale bars are 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/227163/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="446">
Fig 
<number box="[646,675,1787,1811]" pageId="2" pageNumber="446" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view, Y-shaped; basiventral process short. Styles (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 19" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[167,1421,376,1877]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,373,1900]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 19. Portanus hastatus sp. nov. 9 – 14, male genitalia. 9, genital chamber, lateral view. 10, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view. 11, connective and right style, dorsal view. 12, right style, lateral view. 13, aedeagus, lateral view. 14, aedeagus, caudal view. 15 – 19, female genitalia. 15, sternite VII, ventral view. 16, pygofer, lateral view. 17, gonoplac, lateral view. 18, valvula I, lateral view. 19, valvulae II, lateral view. All scale bars are 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/227163/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="446">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,223,1823,1847]" pageId="2" pageNumber="446" value="11.5" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="11.0">11–12</number>
</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view, with apical fourth wide and appearing bifid because of an elongate and robust preapical lobe; apex acute. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[474,599,1859,1884]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 19" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[167,1421,376,1877]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,373,1900]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 19. Portanus hastatus sp. nov. 9 – 14, male genitalia. 9, genital chamber, lateral view. 10, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view. 11, connective and right style, dorsal view. 12, right style, lateral view. 13, aedeagus, lateral view. 14, aedeagus, caudal view. 15 – 19, female genitalia. 15, sternite VII, ventral view. 16, pygofer, lateral view. 17, gonoplac, lateral view. 18, valvula I, lateral view. 19, valvulae II, lateral view. All scale bars are 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/227163/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="446">
Fig. 
<number box="[526,599,1859,1883]" pageId="2" pageNumber="446" value="13.5" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="13.0">13–14</number>
</figureCitation>
), in lateral view, with short and tubular shaft; short dorsal apodemes; apex with pair of elongate straight processes directed dorsally and acute.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1643,2028]" pageId="2" pageNumber="446">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,403,1931,1956]" pageId="2" pageNumber="446">Female genitalia.</emphasis>
Sternite VII (
<figureCitation box="[559,641,1931,1956]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 19" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[167,1421,376,1877]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,373,1900]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 19. Portanus hastatus sp. nov. 9 – 14, male genitalia. 9, genital chamber, lateral view. 10, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view. 11, connective and right style, dorsal view. 12, right style, lateral view. 13, aedeagus, lateral view. 14, aedeagus, caudal view. 15 – 19, female genitalia. 15, sternite VII, ventral view. 16, pygofer, lateral view. 17, gonoplac, lateral view. 18, valvula I, lateral view. 19, valvulae II, lateral view. All scale bars are 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/227163/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="446">
Fig. 
<number box="[612,641,1931,1956]" pageId="2" pageNumber="446" value="15.0">15</number>
</figureCitation>
) approximately rectangular; posterior margin slightly convex. Pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[159,243,1967,1992]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 19" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[167,1421,376,1877]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,373,1900]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 19. Portanus hastatus sp. nov. 9 – 14, male genitalia. 9, genital chamber, lateral view. 10, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view. 11, connective and right style, dorsal view. 12, right style, lateral view. 13, aedeagus, lateral view. 14, aedeagus, caudal view. 15 – 19, female genitalia. 15, sternite VII, ventral view. 16, pygofer, lateral view. 17, gonoplac, lateral view. 18, valvula I, lateral view. 19, valvulae II, lateral view. All scale bars are 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/227163/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="446">
Fig. 
<number box="[214,243,1967,1992]" pageId="2" pageNumber="446" value="16.0">16</number>
</figureCitation>
) lobe longer than high; dorsal margin with concavity at apical third; long macrosetae distributed along ventral margin, more concentrated at apical half; microsetae along dorso-apical margin; apex narrowly round.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,320]" pageId="3" pageNumber="447">
Gonoplac (
<figureCitation box="[279,363,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 19" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[167,1421,376,1877]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,373,1900]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 19. Portanus hastatus sp. nov. 9 – 14, male genitalia. 9, genital chamber, lateral view. 10, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view. 11, connective and right style, dorsal view. 12, right style, lateral view. 13, aedeagus, lateral view. 14, aedeagus, caudal view. 15 – 19, female genitalia. 15, sternite VII, ventral view. 16, pygofer, lateral view. 17, gonoplac, lateral view. 18, valvula I, lateral view. 19, valvulae II, lateral view. All scale bars are 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/227163/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="447">
Fig. 
<number box="[335,363,152,176]" pageId="3" pageNumber="447" value="17.0">17</number>
</figureCitation>
) with basal half distinctly narrower than apical half; microsetae distributed near apex; apex acute. Valvulae I (
<figureCitation box="[351,431,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 19" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[167,1421,376,1877]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,373,1900]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 19. Portanus hastatus sp. nov. 9 – 14, male genitalia. 9, genital chamber, lateral view. 10, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view. 11, connective and right style, dorsal view. 12, right style, lateral view. 13, aedeagus, lateral view. 14, aedeagus, caudal view. 15 – 19, female genitalia. 15, sternite VII, ventral view. 16, pygofer, lateral view. 17, gonoplac, lateral view. 18, valvula I, lateral view. 19, valvulae II, lateral view. All scale bars are 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/227163/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="447">
Fig. 
<number box="[403,431,188,212]" pageId="3" pageNumber="447" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
) with dorsal sculpturing strigate and ventral sculpturing maculose; apex acute. Valvulae II (
<figureCitation box="[159,241,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 19" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[167,1421,376,1877]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,373,1900]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 19. Portanus hastatus sp. nov. 9 – 14, male genitalia. 9, genital chamber, lateral view. 10, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view. 11, connective and right style, dorsal view. 12, right style, lateral view. 13, aedeagus, lateral view. 14, aedeagus, caudal view. 15 – 19, female genitalia. 15, sternite VII, ventral view. 16, pygofer, lateral view. 17, gonoplac, lateral view. 18, valvula I, lateral view. 19, valvulae II, lateral view. All scale bars are 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/227163/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="447">
Fig. 
<number box="[212,241,224,248]" pageId="3" pageNumber="447" value="19.0">19</number>
</figureCitation>
) with apical half expanded, narrowing to apex; dorsal surface with 
<number box="[1006,1034,223,248]" pageId="3" pageNumber="447" value="25.0">25</number>
continuous teeth, each subquadrate and without denticles; numerous anastomosed ducts extending to bases of teeth; apex without preapical ventral prominence or denticles.
</paragraph>
