<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="448" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,151,680]" pageId="4" pageNumber="448">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,151,176]" pageId="4" pageNumber="448">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[323,527,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Portanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hastatus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[323,527,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="448">Portanus hastatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[536,627,151,176]" pageId="4" pageNumber="448" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[536,627,151,176]" pageId="4" pageNumber="448">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is very similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Carvalho &amp; Cavichioli, 2001" authorityName="Carvalho &amp; Cavichioli" authorityYear="2001" box="[836,1284,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Portanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mariae">
<emphasis box="[836,944,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="448">P. mariae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Carvalho" box="[952,1284,151,176]" pageId="4" pageNumber="448" refString="Carvalho, A. N. &amp; Cavichioli, R. R. (2001) Portanus Ball: descricoes de cinco especies novas (Hemiptera, Auchenorryncha, Cicadellidae, Xestocephalinae) do Mato Grosso, Brasil. Revista Brasileira de Zoologia, 18 (3), 855 - 867. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1590 / s 0101 - 81752001000300022" type="journal article" year="2001">
Carvalho &amp; Cavichioli, 
<number box="[1225,1284,152,176]" pageId="4" pageNumber="448" value="2001.0">2001</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, both species sharing the: (
<number box="[310,322,188,212]" pageId="4" pageNumber="448" value="1.0">1</number>
) shape of ivory maculae on crown apex; (
<number box="[835,850,188,212]" pageId="4" pageNumber="448" value="2.0">2</number>
) ventroapical margins of male pygofer acute and ventrally projected; and (
<number box="[443,457,224,248]" pageId="4" pageNumber="448" value="3.0">3</number>
) pair of elongate aedeagal apical process directed anterodorsally. However, the new species can be distinguished from the latter and other 
<taxonomicName box="[780,883,261,284]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Portanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[780,883,261,284]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="448">Portanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species by its shorter aedeagal shaft and dorsal apodemes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="448" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,151,680]" pageId="4" pageNumber="448">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,332,357]" pageId="4" pageNumber="448">Etymology.</emphasis>
